                <h1>Understanding Marginalized Groups: A Path to Inclusivity</h1>
                <p>Marginalized groups face systemic inequities that limit their access to resources, rights, and opportunities. This includes racial minorities, LGBTQ+ individuals, the disabled, and low-income communities. Understanding their struggles is essential in fostering inclusivity and advocating for social justice, allowing everyone to thrive equally.</p>
